headline: Accenture Partners With U.S. Department of Energy to Support Groundbreaking Genesis Mission Program
summary: ARLINGTON, Va., December 18, 2025--Accenture Federal Services, a wholly owned subsidiary of Accenture (NYSE: ACN), announced today its agreement to explore partnerships with the U.S. Department of Energy (DOE) to support the Genesis Mission. This era-defining initiative is a national imperative that will accelerate American leadership in the global Artificial Intelligence (AI) race and fundamentally transform the nation's science and technology ecosystem.

headline: Accenture’s (NYSE:ACN) Q4 CY2025 Sales Beat Estimates
summary: Global professional services company Accenture (NYSE:ACN) reported revenue ahead of Wall Streets expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 6% year on year to $18.74 billion. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $17.68 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.94 per share was 5.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Accenture beats quarterly revenue estimate on strong demand for AI services
summary: Accenture beat Wall Street expectations for first-quarter revenue on Thursday, buoyed by robust demand ​for its artificial intelligence-driven IT services as the ‌company advances its AI strategy to capture greater market share.  "I am very pleased with our $21 billion in new bookings, including ‍33 clients with quarterly bookings greater than $100 million," said CEO Julie Sweet.  Accenture partnered with top AI startups Anthropic and OpenAI earlier this ​month to train its employees on their models and ‌familiarize with their latest capabilities to upskill workers and stay ahead of competitors.
